  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the robata grill to medium-high heat (400°F).",
    "Rinse the cod fillets and pat them dry with paper towels.",
    "Season the cod with fish seasoning, salt, and black pepper.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together minced garlic, smoked paprika, and dried dill weed.",
    "Brush the cod fillets with olive oil and apply the garlic-paprika-dill mixture evenly.",
    "Place the cod fillets on the preheated grill and cook for 3-4 minutes per side, or until cooked through.",
    "Transfer the cooked cod to a plate and sprinkle with crushed almonds, chopped parsley, and crumbled feta cheese.",
    "Drizzle with lemon juice and serve hot."
